    • onNewToken

      public static void onNewToken​(android.content.Context context, java.lang.String token)
      Method to be called in your own FirebaseMessagingService to handle WonderPush push notifications. Note: This is only required if you use your own FirebaseMessagingService. Implement your FirebaseMessagingService.onNewToken(String) method as follows: 
      @Override
 public void onNewToken(String token) {
     WonderPushFirebaseMessagingService.onNewToken(this, token);
     // Do your own handling here
 }
      Parameters:
      context - The current context
      token - The received token

    • onMessageReceived

      public static boolean onMessageReceived​(android.content.Context context, com.google.firebase.messaging.RemoteMessage message)
      Method to be called in your own FirebaseMessagingService to handle WonderPush push notifications. Note: This is only required if you use your own FirebaseMessagingService. Implement your FirebaseMessagingService.onMessageReceived(RemoteMessage) method as follows: 
      @Override
 public void onMessageReceived(RemoteMessage message) {
     if (WonderPushFirebaseMessagingService.onMessageReceived(this, message)) {
         return;
     }
     // Do your own handling here
 }
      Parameters:
      context - The current context
      message - The received message
      Returns:
      Whether the notification has been handled by WonderPush
